    "body": "I have the exact same issue on Ubuntu 23.04. Pretty fresh install, did it just today. If it helps, here is the output of the above commands:\r\n\r\n```\r\necho $TMPDIR $TEMPDIR\r\n\r\n$ mktemp\r\n/tmp/tmp.5igkJVTYUl\r\n\r\n$ ls /tmp\r\ndbus-15tMpvrs\r\ndbus-BSa7bdKK\r\nsnap-private-tmp\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-bluetooth.service-40PiT8\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-colord.service-iWDWjV\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-fwupd.service-GhDbkQ\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-ModemManager.service-e0shnV\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-power-profiles-daemon.service-lJpxt2\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-switcheroo-control.service-GD5Vqn\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-systemd-logind.service-oldBHl\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-systemd-oomd.service-sE0Yqc\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-systemd-resolved.service-pctiSF\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-systemd-timedated.service-SzpWpw\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-systemd-timesyncd.service-3j3bBB\r\nsystemd-private-492516dfc5ae486d917be5b7a48c7c56-upower.service-PjWRSJ\r\ntmp.5igkJVTYUl\r\ntmp.riBXaU34o4\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo be honest, I'm wondering if it's some weird permission issue. Tried installing Oh-My-Posh, and it fails because it can't find the files it downloaded. Tried installing Homebrew and that one fails to download some files as well. Maybe something gets corrupted while downloading from GitHub? Something wrong with tar when asked to open the downloaded archives?",
