    "body": "@chipbuster \r\n\r\nHere's the output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n~$ url=\"https://github.com/starship/starship/releases/download/v1.16.0/starship-x86_64-unknown-linux-musl.tar.gz\"\r\n\r\n~$ echo $url\r\nhttps://github.com/starship/starship/releases/download/v1.16.0/starship-x86_64-unknown-linux-musl.tar.gz\r\n\r\n~$ file=\"$(mktemp).tar.gz\"\r\n~$ echo $file\r\n/tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi.tar.gz\r\n\r\n~$ curl --fail --silent --location --output $file $url\r\n\r\n~$ cd /tmp\r\n/tmp$ ls\r\ndbus-AyGoyovb\r\ndbus-DbhqFg4X\r\nsnap-private-tmp\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-bluetooth.service-MEXXbm\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-colord.service-JIYBdh\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-fwupd.service-31T7oN\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-ModemManager.service-wfEPrx\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-power-profiles-daemon.service-hWwAbi\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-switcheroo-control.service-vHgYis\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-systemd-logind.service-YmZE3L\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-systemd-oomd.service-FHp3iT\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-systemd-resolved.service-yBoAAF\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-systemd-timesyncd.service-bbqnqF\r\nsystemd-private-f777e752c6b94c54b4d7e0ab02153186-upower.service-8dFg8X\r\ntmp.ouRILl1Dhi\r\ntracker-extract-3-files.1000\r\n\r\n/tmp$ cd ~\r\n~$ ls\r\nDesktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Public  snap  Templates  Videos\r\n~$ tar -xzvof $file\r\ntar (child): /tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi.tar.gz: Cannot open: No such file or directory\r\ntar (child): Error is not recoverable: exiting now\r\ntar: Child returned status 2\r\ntar: Error is not recoverable: exiting now\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like `curl` is not behaving as expected. It's told to create `/tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi.tar.gz` but it only creates `/tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi`. Or am I misunderstanding something here?",
