    "body": "> Looks like curl is not behaving as expected. It's told to create /tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi.tar.gz but it only creates /tmp/tmp.ouRILl1Dhi.\r\n\r\nThat's exactly the conclusion I came to.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure why it would be doing this, although [there have previously been issues noted with curl installed through snap misbehaving](https://askubuntu.com/questions/1387141/curl-23-failure-writing-output-to-destination).\r\n\r\nDo you know if you have curl installed through snap or apt? If it's snap, could you try reinstalling with apt and trying again?",
